OL,3,CThe charity helping cancer patients
OL,4,Cmeet 13,000 appointments a year
OL,6,F"We get told (by) some of them (that
OL,7,Fthey) wouldn't make the journey, they
OL,8,Fwouldn't have the treatment," he said.
OL,9,F"And that's it really - if they're not
OL,10,Fgoing to have the treatment, they're
OL,11,Fpotentially not going to survive.
OL,13,F"This has been our busiest since we've
OL,14,Fbeen formed and currently we are going
OL,15,Fto hit 13,000 appointments this year.
OL,17,F"There is no-one that we turn away. As
OL,18,Flong as they live in the area of
OL,19,FDoncaster, Retford, Worksop,
OL,20,FRotherham, we will take them, it's not
OL,21,Fa problem to us."
